description: Given by Explorer Jack in Lumbridge for completing all Beginner Tasks in Lumbridge.
name: Lumbridge Set Tasks - Beginner
reward:
Explorer's ring 1 and a magic lamp worth 500xp in a skill of your choice.
The ring provides the following benefits:
- Recharge 50% of your run energy once per day.
- Slight boost to Prayer and Magic.
- Access to the Explore emote.

description: Given by Bob, the axe seller in Lumbridge, for completing all Easy Tasks in Lumbridge.
name: Lumbridge Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Explorer's ring 2 and a magic lamp worth 1,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The ring gains the following extra benefits:
- Recharge 50% of your run energy twice per day.
- Cast Low-level Alchemy without runes, 30 times per day.
- 10% chance per essence of receiving extra elemental runes from runecrafting.

description: Given by Rat Burgiss south of Varrock for completing all Easy Tasks in Varrock.
name: Varrock Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Varrock armour 1 and a magic lamp worth 1,000XP in a skill of your choice.
The armour gives the following benefits:
- +4% chance for double smelting bronze, iron, steel.
- +4% chance for double ore mining copper, tin, iron, coal.
- +4% chance for double progress smithing bronze, iron, steel
- Improved chance of receiving a skull sceptre piece in the Stronghold of Security.
You may also talk to Rat to change your Varrock Teleport destination to the Grand Exchange.
Naff will sell up to 16 battlestaves a day.

description: Given by Redbeard Frank in Port Sarim for completing all Easy Tasks in Falador.
name: Falador Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Falador shield 1 and a magic lamp worth 1,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The shield confers the following benefits:
- Recharge 25% of your Prayer points once per day.
- Allows you to perform an emote using the shield when it is wielded.

description: Given by Grand Vizier Hassan in either Al Kharid Palace or Menaphos Merchant District for completing all Easy Tasks in the Kharidian desert.
name: Desert Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Desert amulet 1 and a magic lamp worth 2,000 XP in a skill of your choice.
A daily bag of lost & found items from a rug merchant.
Sparkly dung kalphites drop double loot.
2% cheaper prices in the pizazz store.
Double water from cacti.

description: Given by Hiylik Myna, east of Paterdomus, for completing all Easy Tasks in Morytania.
name: Morytania Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Morytania legs 1 and a magic lamp worth 4,000XP in a skill of your choice.
The legs confer the following benefits:
- Double fungi when casting Bloom.
- 5% extra Temple Trekking rewards.
- 50% chance of a ghast ignoring you rather than attacking.

description: Given by Pirate Jackie the Fruit outside Brimhaven Agility Arena for completing all Easy Tasks in Karamja.
name: Karamja Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Karamja gloves 1 and a magic lamp worth 1,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The gloves confer the following benefits:
- Half-price travel on the Port Sarim-Musa Point and Ardougne-Brimhaven boats (15gp).
- You may claim 40 pineapples a day from Dell Monti.

description: Given by any seer in Seers' Village for completing all Easy Tasks in Seers' Village.
name: Seers' Village Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Seers' headband 1 and a magic lamp worth 1,000 XP in a skill of your choice.
The coal trucks at the Seers' Village coal mine will now hold 252 coal.
The headband confers the following benefits:
- Provides a constant source of weak light (subsequent headbands will provide stronger light).
- 100% chance of receiving two logs when cutting normal trees.
Geoffrey in the flax field near Seers' Village will give you 30 flax per day.

description: Given by the council workman on the bridge south of Rellekka for completing all Easy Tasks in the Fremennik Province.
name: Fremennik Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Fremennik sea boots 1 and a magic lamp worth 5,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The boots confer the following benefits:
- Contact the Fossegrimmen at a distance to recharge your lyre with one fewer charge.
Peer the Seer will deposit items into your bank for you.
When charging your lyre at the Fossegrimmen's altar you will receive one extra charge.

description: Given by Doctor Orbon in Ardougne Church for completing all Easy Tasks in Ardougne.
name: Ardougne Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Ardougne cloak 1 and a magic lamp worth 1,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The cloak confers the following benefits:
- Unlimited teleports to the monastery south of Ardougne.
- 40% of items dropped in the Tower of Life will be noted.
- Improved rate of success when stealing from stalls in East Ardougne's market.
You will be able to sell cats to citizens for double the normal number of death runes.
On entering a game of Castle Wars your Prayer points will be boosted by 10%.
- 25% chance of two chompy birds appearing when chompy hunting.

description: Given by the elf tracker near the Tirannwn lodestone for completing all Easy Tasks in Tirannwn.
name: Tirannwn Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Tirannwn quiver 1 and a magic lamp worth 10,000 XP in a skill of your choice.
Permanent, passive benefits:
- Access to an elf to whom you can sell your limestone near the limestone rocks; 5% damage boost against Mourners; 15 free swamp tar per day from the Lletya General Store.
While wearing the quiver:
- Allows you to always pass through leaf traps succesfully, and acts as a chime for the warped creatures in the Poison Waste Dungeon.
- Grants access to a shortcut deeper into the Poison Waste Dungeon; 5% chance of tortoise shells being noted.
- Ability to teleport to Lletya, and to Eluned, wherever she is in the forest, or Islywn if Eluned is unavailable.

description: Given by Drangund, the Dungeoneering Tutor, in the camp for completing all Easy Tasks in Daemonheim.
name: Daemonheim Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Daemonheim aura 1 and a magic lamp worth 2,000 XP in a skill of your choice.
The aura confers the following benefits:
- Access to a Heim crab weapon cosmetic override.
- Ability to choose at the start of a dungeon which boss you encounter once per day.
- Choose a secondary ring role which has 25% its normal effect.
Whilst wearing the aura:
- One consequence free death per day whilst in a dungeon.

description: Given by Mr Ex, north of Edgeville bank, for completing all Easy Tasks in the Wilderness.
name: Wilderness Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Permanent benefits:
- Free teleports to the Wilderness Farming patch, using the Wilderness sword
- Free teleports to Edgeville, using the Wilderness sword.

description: Given by Ned in Draynor Village for completing all Medium Tasks in Lumbridge.

reward:
Explorer's ring 3 and a magic lamp worth 1,500xp in a skill of your choice.
The ring gains the following extra benefits:
- Recharge 50% of your run energy three times per day.
- Free teleports to the cabbage field south of Falador.

description: Given by Reldo in Varrock Palace's library for completing all Medium Tasks in Varrock.
name: Varrock Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Varrock armour 2 and a magic lamp worth 5,000XP in a skill of your choice.
The armour gains the following extra benefits:
- +3% chance for double smelting mithril, adamant.
- +3% chance for double ore mining mithril, adamantite, luminite.
- +3% chance for double progress smithing mithril, adamant.
- Further improved chance of receiving a skull sceptre piece in the Stronghold of Security.
- Skull sceptres have additional charges if assembled while wearing the armour.
Naff will sell up to 32 battlestaves a day.

description: Given by the chemist in Rimmington for completing all Medium Tasks in Falador.
name: Falador Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Falador shield 2 and a magic lamp worth 5,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The shield gains the following extra benefits:
- Recharge 50% of your Prayer points once per day.
- You will receive a 10% experience bonus from farming the patches north of Port Sarim while this shield is wielded.

description: Given by Zahur in Nardah for completing all Medium Tasks in the Kharidian desert.
name: Desert Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Desert amulet 2 and a magic lamp worth 8,000 XP in a skill of your choice. 20 noted potato cacti per day, claimed from the Weird Old Man.
Sceptre of the Gods can now store 20 charges.
The amulet gains the following benefits:
- Goats have chance to drop noted goat horn.
- Unlimited teleport to Nardah.
- Ability to create 50 molten glass with only pot ash while outside in the desert.
- Reduced failure rate on the Agility Pyramid.
- 5% cheaper prices in the pizazz store and a second teak tree near Uzer.

description: Given by Robin, in Port Phasmatys, for completing all Medium Tasks in Morytania.
name: Morytania Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Morytania legs 2 and a magic lamp worth 10,000XP in a skill of your choice. Robin offers 13 lots of bonemeal in exchange for bones, and 13 free buckets of slime per day. Razmire offers a daily choice of free planks, upgrades all olive oil vials being bought from his shop to 4 doses for free and lets you use the pyre log storage chests in Mort'ton.
The legs gain the following additional benefits:
- Ability to teleport to the slime pit under the Ectofuntus 5 times daily.
- Cannonball-smithing time is halved in Port Phasmatys.
- The mushroom patch near Canifis will no longer become diseased.
- Haunted tools will no longer attack you in the Abandoned Mine.

description: Given by Kaleb Paramaya in Shilo Village for completing all Medium Tasks in Karamja.
name: Karamja Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Karamja gloves 2 and a magic lamp worth 5,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The gloves gain the following extra benefits:
- 10% experience bonus from the Brimhaven Agility Arena.

description: Given by Stankers at the coal mine west of Seers' Village for completing all Medium Tasks in Seers' Village.
name: Seers' Village Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Seers' headband 2 and a magic lamp worth 5,000 XP in a skill of your choice. The coal trucks at the Seers' Village coal mine will now hold 280 coal.
The headband gains the following extra benefits:
- 10% bonus experience when cutting maple trees.
- Faster spinning when using the spinning wheel in Seers' Village.
Geoffrey in the flax field near Seers' Village will give you 60 flax per day.

description: Given by Yrsa in Rellekka for completing all Medium Tasks in the Fremennik Province.
name: Fremennik Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Fremennik sea boots 2 and a magic lamp worth 10,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The boots gain the following extra benefits:
- One chargeless teleport with the lyre per day.
- Shortcut between the piers of Etceteria and Miscellania.
Your kingdom's approval rating will increase faster.

description: Given by the town crier in East Ardougne's market for completing all Medium Tasks in Ardougne.
name: Ardougne Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Ardougne cloak 2 and a magic lamp worth 7,500xp in a skill of your choice. Wizard Cromperty will offer you 100 noted essence per day.
The cloak gains the following extra benefits:
- Teleport to the Farming patch north of Ardougne once per day.
- Improved rate of success when picking pockets in Ardougne.
- Double length PvP immunity after pulling the Wilderness teleport lever.
- 60% of items dropped in the Tower of Life will be noted.
- Improved yield from crafting runes at Ourania Altar.
Talk to the town crier to toggle your ring of life teleport destination to Ardougne.
- 50% chance of two chompy birds appearing when chompy hunting.

description: Given by Gwir in Lletya for completing all Medium Tasks in Tirannwn.
name: Tirannwn Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Tirannwn quiver 2 and a magic lamp worth 30,000 XP in a skill of your choice.
Permanent, passive benefits:
- Access to a new mushroom patch near Tyras Camp; an increase to 30 swamp tar per day from the Lletya General Store; 5% damage boost against shadow creatures.
- 5% chance of not using a charge on your crystal bow and wards and the ability to catch grenwalls without baiting traps.
While wearing the quiver:
- Prevents poison from traps in the forest.
- Tyras Camp and Poison Waste Slayer Dungeon teleports are available.

description: Given by Marmaros, the Rewards Trader, in the camp for completing all Medium Tasks in Daemonheim.
name: Daemonheim Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Daemonheim aura 2 and a magic lamp worth 8,000 XP in a skill of your choice. A one off payment of 2,000 Dungeoneering tokens.
The aura gains the following extra benefits:
- Ability to bind one potion in a new slot.
- A supply of law and cosmic runes available from the Smuggler for free in every dungeon.
- Secondary ring role effect is boosted to 50%
- Access to an extended portion of the resource dungeon on the Daemonheim Peninsula.
Whilst wearing the aura:
- The aura will act like Ava's Accumulator and the bonecrusher, whilst inside Daemonheim.

description: Given by Mandrith, near the Pirates' Hideout in the Wilderness, for completing all Medium Tasks in the Wilderness.
name: Wilderness Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Permanent benefits:
- All of the benefits from the easy task set.
- +5% XP per lap completion at the Wilderness Agility course with the Wilderness sword equipped or in your inventory.
- Improved pickpocketing rates against Rogues in the Wilderness.
- Free teleports to the Forinthry dungeon, using the Wilderness sword.

description: Given by Ned in Draynor Village for completing all Hard Tasks in Lumbridge.
name: Lumbridge Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Explorer's ring 4 and a magic lamp worth 9,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The ring gains the following extra benefits:
- Cast High-level Alchemy without runes, 15 times per day.
- Cast Superheat Item without runes, 27 times per day.
- 50% chance to cast Bones to Bananas without using up runes, 10 successes per day.
- Claim a hamper of food from Lumbridge Castle's cook, once per day.

description: Given by Vannaka in Edgeville for completing all Hard Tasks in Varrock.
name: Varrock Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Varrock armour 3 and a magic lamp worth 10,000XP in a skill of your choice.
The armour gains the following extra benefits:
- +2% chance for double smelting rune, orikalkum, necronium.
- +2% chance for double ore mining runite, orichalcite, drakolith, necrite, phasmatite.
- +2% chance for double progress smithing rune, orikalkum, necronium.
- Access the Cooking Guild without a chef's hat, and access its bank.
Naff will sell up to 64 battlestaves a day.

description: Given by Sir Vyvin's squire in Falador Castle for completing all Hard Tasks in Falador.
name: Falador Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Falador shield 3 and a magic lamp worth 10,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The shield gains the following extra benefits:
- Recharge 100% of your Prayer points once per day.
- Wysin will trade mole skins for white lily seeds when this shield is carried.

description: Given by Hakeem the Mayor in Pollnivneach for completing all Hard Tasks in the Kharidian desert.
name: Desert Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Desert amulet 3 and a magic lamp worth 20,000 XP in a skill of your choice. 30 noted potato cacti per day, claimed from the Weird Old Man.
10% cheaper prices in the pizazz store.
Double charges from artefacts when recharging the Sceptre of the Gods.
Cactus patches in the desert will be protected from disease and you'll get double the spines.
Half the chance of mummies and scarabs spawning in Pyramid Plunder.
The Keris has a greater chance to score a vicious blow.
The amulet can now produce a total of 100 molten glass per day.
Sceptre of the Gods can now store 60 charges.

description: Given by the Strange Old Man, at the Barrows, for completing all Hard Tasks in Morytania.
name: Morytania Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Morytania legs 3 and a magic lamp worth 20,000XP in a skill of your choice. Robin offers 26 lots of bonemeal in exchange for bones, and 26 free buckets of slime per day.
The legs gain the following additional benefits:
- Ability to teleport to the slime pit under the Ectofuntus 10 times daily.
- Increased chance of gaining better keys from burning shades.
- 50% more Prayer XP by burning shades.
- All ghosts will now talk to you as if you were wearing the Amulet of Ghostspeak.
- Prayer drain in the Barrows is reduced by 50%.
- Receive double runes from Barrows chests.
- 10% more Temple Trekking rewards.
- 50% chance that Blood Altar teletabs don't break on use.
- Access to a shortcut that leads to the Abandoned mine crystal outcrops.

description: Given by any jungle forester north of Kharazi Jungle for completing all Hard Tasks in Karamja.
name: Karamja Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Karamja gloves 3 and a magic lamp worth 10,000xp in a skill of your choice.
The gloves gain the following extra benefits:
- Free entry to Brimhaven Dungeon.
- Access to the gem mine under Shilo Village.
- Free teleport to the Shilo Village gem mine.

description: Given by Sir Kay in Camelot Castle for completing all Hard Tasks in Seers' Village.
name: Seers' Village Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Seers' headband 3 and a magic lamp worth 10,000 XP in a skill of your choice. The coal trucks at the Seers' Village coal mine will now hold 308 coal.

Geoffrey in the flax field near Seers' Village will give you 120 flax per day.

reward:
Fremennik sea boots 3 and a magic lamp worth 15,000xp in a skill of your choice.

Advisor Ghrim will accept flatpack furniture as donations to your kingdom's treasury. Ability to change to Lunar spellbook in Prifddinas.

description: Given by Aleck in Yanille for completing all Hard Tasks in Ardougne.
name: Ardougne Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Ardougne cloak 3 and a magic lamp worth 28,000xp in a skill of your choice. Wizard Cromperty will offer you 150 noted essence per day.
The cloak gains the following extra benefits:
- Improved rate of success when picking pockets or shoplifting from stalls.
- Teleport traps on chests will always teleport you to Ardougne's north bank.
- 80% of items dropped in the Tower of Life will be noted.
Talk to Aleck in Yanille to toggle your Watchtower Teleport destination to Yanille town centre.
- 75% chance of two chompy birds appearing when chompy hunting.

description: Given by Arianwyn in the Cadarn district for completing all Hard Tasks in Tirannwn.
name: Tirannwn Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Tirannwn quiver 3 and a magic lamp worth 40,000 XP in a skill of your choice.
Permanent, passive benefits:
- Lord Amlodd grants 10% more shards back when exchanging pouches; Eilwynn will exchange your divination chronicles.
- Lunet has a daily stash of battlestaves; 5% damage boost against elves.
While wearing the quiver:
- The Corrupted Seren Stone is easier to cleanse.
- Death Altar and Elf Camp teleports are available.
- Allows you to always pass through stick traps succesfully.

description: Given by Talsar in the camp for completing all Hard Tasks in Daemonheim.
name: Daemonheim Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Daemonheim aura 3 and a magic lamp worth 20,000 XP in a skill of your choice. A one off payment of 38,000 Dungeoneering tokens.
The aura gains the following extra benefits:
- Secondary ring role effect is boosted to 75%.
- Access to 2 more bind pool slots.
- Reduced cost for recharging items.
- 10% increase in rewards from sinkholes.
- Access to an extended portion of the resource dungeon in the Dwarven Mine.
Whilst wearing the aura:
- The Backhand ability will now unleash your inner Thok.

description: Given by Quercus, at the ditch north of the Grand Exchange, for completing all Hard Tasks in the Wilderness.
name: Wilderness Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Permanent benefits:
- All of the benefits from the easy & medium task set.
- The ability to un-note items with Harrison near the Chaos altar.
- A new shortcut to the Air Obelisk north of Edgeville.
- Teleporting to the Wilderness lodestone will always be a quick teleport.
- The Wilderness herb patch will never become diseased.
- Ability to choose your arrival destination at the Ancient Obelisks in the Wilderness.
- Chance to teleport to the center of the Abyss when teleporting via the Mage of Zamorak with the Wilderness sword equipped.

description: Given by Vannaka in Edgeville for completing all Elite Tasks in Varrock.
name: Varrock Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Varrock armour 4 and a set of magic lamps worth a total of 150,000XP in four skills of your choice.
The armour gains the following extra benefits:
- +1% chance for double smelting bane, elder rune.
- +1% chance for double ore mining banite, light animica, dark animica.
- +1% chance for double progress smithing bane, elder rune.
The armour gives five free Bolt Enchant spells per day, up to diamond bolts.
Talk to Rat, Reldo or Vannaka to toggle your Varrock Teleport to the north-east of Varrock.
Naff will sell up to 80 battlestaves a day.
The Varrock estate agent offers half-price housing costs.
Bork's drops are more generous.
Access is granted to the log storage chests near each beacon in the beacon network.
Reduced chance of being randomly teleported in the Chaos Tunnels.
Unlimited teleports to Bork's lair.

description: Given by Sir Vyvin's squire in Falador Castle for completing all Elite Tasks in Falador.
name: Falador Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Falador shield 4 and a set of magic lamps worth 160,000xp in four skills of your choice.
The shield gains the following extra benefits:
- Recharge 100% of your Prayer twice per day.
- Receive 5% extra experience and renown in the Artisan's workshop.
- Has all of the benefits of the Anti-dragon Shield (Mole) when facing the Giant mole.
- The mole has a chance of dropping a mole nose, which you may trade with Wyson for higher-value nests.
When using the altar in Falador Castle to recharge Prayer points, you will gain an additional 20 points.
Ability to use the ancient hymnal on the Falador Castle altar to convert it to a Zaros altar.

description: Given by the Golem in Uzer for completing all Elite Tasks in the Kharidian desert.
name: Desert Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Desert amulet 4 and 4 magic lamps, worth a total of 160,000 XP in skills of your choice. 40 noted potato cacti per day, claimed from the Weird Old Man.
Opportunity to reroll your Dominion Tower chest rewards.
20% Chance of making 4-dose super antifire pots.
Two feathers at once from the Phoenix.
Boosted stats on the ancient staff.
Granite buyer at the quarry and a new sandstone rock on the coast near Sophanem.
The amulet can now produce a total of 150 molten glass per day.

description: Given by Old Man Ral, in Meiyerditch, for completing all Elite Tasks in Morytania.
name: Morytania Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Morytania legs 4 and magic lamps worth a total of 140,000XP in a skill of your choice. Robin offers 39 lots of bonemeal in exchange for bones, and 39 free buckets of slime per day.
The legs gain the following additional benefits:
- Ability to teleport to the slime pit under the Ectofuntus 20 times daily.
- Each essence has a 10% chance of gaining a second blood rune at the Blood altar.
- 50% more Prayer XP from burning vyrewatch.
- 20% chance of creating a 4-dose prayer renewal potion when making it in Morytania.
- 10% additional Slayer XP for kills in the Slayer Tower when on a task.
- Double mushroom yield on the patch near Canifis.

description: Given by any jungle forester north of Kharazi Jungle for completing all Elite Tasks in Karamja.
name: Karamja Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Karamja gloves 4 and a set of magic lamps worth a total of 140,000xp in three skills of your choice.
The gloves gain the following extra benefits:
- 25% chance of receiving double tickets in Brimhaven Agility Arena.
- Once per day, if I am killed in the Fight Cave/Pit, I will be resurrected on the spot.
Double damage against wild dogs in Brimhaven Dungeon, and access to a shortcut to the red dragon area of the dungeon.
Lapalok will give me more Slayer points.
Once per day, the TzHaar banker will give me 8,000 Tok-Kul and Dell Monti will give me 40 apples.
I can now use the shortcut into Shilo village.

description: Given by Sir Kay in Camelot Castle for completing all Elite Tasks in Seers' Village.
name: Seers' Village Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Seers' headband 4 and a set of magic lamps worth 145,000 XP in five skills of your choice.
The headband gains the following extra benefits:
- The Camelot Teleport spell will teleport you to the centre of Seers' Village.
Up to 200 coal a day will be transferred directly to your bank if placed in the coal trucks.
Increased chance of activating the special effect of an enchanted bolt.
Geoffrey in the flax field near Seers' Village will give you 200 flax per day.

description: Given by Advisor Ghrim in Miscellania for completing all Elite Tasks in the Fremennik Province.
name: Fremennik Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Fremennik sea boots 4 and a set of magic lamps worth a total of 160,000xp in five skills of your choice.
The boots gain the following extra benefits:
- The Dagannoth Kings will drop some items noted.
- Unlimited teleports to the centre of Rellekka market.
- I will also deal more damage to the Dagannoth Kings.
- I can access a new section of Jatizso's mine.
Talk to Rimae Sirsalis to exchange Suqah hide and teeth for rune essence. Use the seal of passage to teleport to Lunar Isle. Use the NPC contact spell to change your Lunar spellbook to the standard spellbook.
Talk to Olaf the Bard in Rellekka to toggle your lyre teleport to Jatizso, Neitiznot, Miscellania or Etceteria.

description: Given by Aleck in Yanille for completing all Elite Tasks in Ardougne.
name: Ardougne Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Ardougne cloak 4 and 4 magic lamps worth 50,000xp each in a skill of your choice. Bert the Sandman will offer you 120 buckets of sand per day.
The cloak gains the following extra benefits:
- Unlimited teleports to the Farming patch north of Ardougne.
- Recharge 100% of your Summoning points once per day.
- The least valuable rewards from the Fishing Trawler will now be more valuable.
- 5% chance of smithing two rune crossbow limbs at once in Yanille.
- Guaranteed chance of two chompy birds appearing when chompy hunting.

description: Given by Elen at the Max Guild for completing all Elite Tasks in Tirannwn.
name: Tirannwn Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Tirannwn quiver 4 and 3 magic lamps, worth a total of 160,000 XP in skills of your choice.
Permanent, passive benefits:
- Daily logs from Coeden; a chance to not use charges on a most wanted card; 5% damage boost against dark beasts.
- 5% chance of not using a charge on your attuned crystal bow and wards.
While wearing the quiver:
- Ability to take a portrait at the photo booth with the head of one of the 8 elf lords.
- Double the blossoms harvested from the crystal acorn tree.
- Ability to fast travel through Tirannwn dense forests while wearing the quiver.

description: Given by Thok in the camp for completing all Elite Tasks in Daemonheim.
name: Daemonheim Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Daemonheim aura 4, 1 magic lamp worth 60,000 XP and 3 magic lamps worth 50,000 XP each in a skill of your choice.
The aura gains the following extra benefits:
- Secondary ring role effect is boosted to 100%.
- 10% discount from the Smuggler.
- Access to Daemonheim hard mode.
- Access to an extended portion of the resource dungeon in the Brimhaven dungeon.
Whilst wearing the aura:
- Second gatestone and teleport spell.
When activated in Daemonheim the aura will grant prayer points when bones are buried.

description: Given by Kolodion, in the Mage Arena bank, for completing all Elite Tasks in the Wilderness.
name: Wilderness Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Permanent benefits:
- All of the benefits from the easy, medium & hard task set.
- Searing ashes will always drop noted when carrying the Wilderness sword.
- One free teleport per day to a Wilderness Warband camp, using the Wilderness sword.
- Free teleports to the Wilderness Agility course with the Wilderness sword.
- Teleports with the Wilderness sword will work from level 30 Wilderness up from level 20.
- Improved Ancient warrior equipment drop rates when defeating revenants in the Forinthry dungeon.
- When in the Wilderness, completion of the Animal Magnetism quest will allow team capes to provide the effects of the Ava's device.

description: Given by Icthlarin, near the ritual site in the City of Um, for completing all Easy Tasks in the Underworld.
name: Underworld Set Tasks - Easy
reward:
Underworld Grimoire 1 and 1 magic lamp, worth 2,000 XP in a skill of your choice (level 20+).
Permanent, passive benefits:
- 15 daily bones from Lupe.
On the grimoire:
- Free teleports to the Um smithy (10/day).
While wearing the grimoire:
- Picked up ashes are sent to the bank.
- Dropped bones and big bones are sent to the focus storage (toggleable).
- 10% chance to make 4-dose necromancy potions while in Um.
- 2.5% chance per impure essence of receiving extra runes from runecrafting.
- +3% XP from dispelling ritual disturbances.

description: Given by Frank, east of the main plaza in Um, for completing all Medium Tasks in the Underworld.
name: Underworld Set Tasks - Medium
reward:
Underworld Grimoire 2 and 1 magic lamp, worth 10,000 XP in a skill of your choice (level 50+).
You gain the following extra permanent, passive benefits:
- 5 daily baby dragon bones, regular ghostly ink and regular ritual candles from Lupe.
The grimoire gains the following extra benefits:
-Unlimited free teleports to the Um smithy.
- Free teleports to the Um/Ungael ritual sites (10/day).
The grimoire gains the following extra benefits while worn:
- Dropped baby dragon bones and wyvern bones are sent to the focus storage (toggleable).
- 10% chance to make 4-dose super necromancy potions while in Um.
- 5% chance per impure essence of receiving extra runes from runecrafting.
- +6% XP from dispelling ritual disturbances.
- +5% necroplasm from rituals.

description: Given by Kili, by the smithy in Um, for completing all Hard Tasks in the Underworld.
name: Underworld Set Tasks - Hard
reward:
Underworld Grimoire 3 and 1 magic lamp, worth 25,000 XP in a skill of your choice (level 70+).
You gain the following extra permanent, passive benefits:
- 5 daily dragon bones, 3 greater ghostly ink and greater ritual candles from Lupe.
- Lupe will now sell 10 buckets of slime daily.
- The mushroom patch in Um will no longer become diseased.
The grimoire gains the following extra benefits:
- Unlimited free teleports to the Um/Ungael ritual site.
The grimoire gains the following extra benefits while worn:
- Dropped dragon bones, dagannoth bones, airut bones, ourg bones, hardened dragon bones and dragonkin bones are sent to the focus storage (toggleable).
- 10% chance to make 4-dose extreme necromancy potions while in Um.
- 7.5% chance per impure essence of receiving extra runes from runecrafting.
- +9% XP from dispelling ritual disturbances.
- +10% necroplasm from rituals.

description: Given by Crunchy, in The Last Call in Um, for completing all Elite Tasks in the Underworld.
name: Underworld Set Tasks - Elite
reward:
Underworld Grimoire 4 and 1 magic lamp, worth 40,000 XP in a skill of your choice (level 80+).
You gain the following extra permanent, passive benefits:
- 2 daily powerful ghostly ink from Lupe.
- Lupe will now put daily rewards in your bank and focus storage.
- 10% chance to make 4-dose necromancy, super necromancy and extreme necromancy potions.
- First death every day is free.
The grimoire gains the following extra benefits:
- Daily free teleport to Lupe.
The grimoire gains the following extra benefits while worn:
- Dropped dinosaur bones, frost dragon bones and reinforced dragon bones are sent to the focus storage (toggleable).
- 10% chance per impure essence of receiving extra runes from runecrafting.
- +12% XP from dispelling ritual disturbances.
- +15% necroplasm from rituals.
